# Plain PHP Coursework Rule

- Keep implementation plain PHP and easy to explain in team discussions.
- Prefer small functions and explicit control flow over heavy abstractions.
- Validate all request input server-side before DB writes.
- Enforce role/ownership checks in every action endpoint.
- Escape all rendered user content with `e()`.
- Keep docs updated in `docs/` when behavior changes.
